Remove casings from sausage links; discard casings. Cut sausage crosswise into 1/2 -inch pieces. In large skillet, cook sausage over medium heat until well browned; drain. Add water to skillet with sausage; bring to a boil. Slowly stir in pasta and seasonings. Reduce heat to medium. Boil uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Meanwhile, cut zucchini and tomatoes lengthwise in half; cut crosswise into slices. Add zucchini to skillet and continue boiling 3 to 5 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring frequently. Stir in tomatoes. Remove skillet from heat. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.